      CREATE (s)-[:REL]->(a),
             (s)-[:REL]->(b),
             (a)-[:REL]->(c),
             (b)-[:LOOP]->(b)
      """
    When executing query:
      """
      MATCH (a:A), (b:C)
      OPTIONAL MATCH (x)-->(b)
      RETURN x
      """
    Then the result should be, in any order:
      | x              |
      | (:A {num: 42}) |
    And no side effects

  Scenario: [4] Optionally matching relationship with bound nodes in reverse direction
